	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Five people have died after a truck tried to overtake two vehicles on the R33 near Doringfontein on the Vaalwater road on Thursday, Arrive Alive said in a statement. "A Toyota Dyna truck tried to overtake two motor vehicles and collided head-on with an oncoming [Volkswagen] minibus. The Dyna truck overturned." The 56-year-old driver of the truck and the four passengers of the minibus - two men and two women - were all declared dead. The driver and four passengers of the minibus were seriously injured, the statement read. SAPS Nylstroom is reportedly investigating the accident.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  